e then followed a profession in teaching while giving several stage performances as a trained Bharatnatyam dancer. During one of these dance performances, it is claimed that Nita met the Ambani family when Dhirubhai Ambani noticed how lively Nita was and approached her with a marriage proposal for his son, Mukesh Ambani. Although their relationship quickly developed into one of love and friendship rather than an arranged marriage, Nita Ambani only consented to marry him if she could keep up her teaching career. Because of her humble beginnings, Nita Ambani maintained her groundedness despite getting married off to a billionaire. She avoided the spotlight for a very long period since she was focused on raising her three children, Akash, Isha, and Anant. Even though Nita Ambani had to cease teaching eventually, she found it difficult to contain her enthusiasm for very long. While Mukesh Ambani was engaged in installing pipelines in Patalganga, she urged that they construct schools in the nearby rural communities. This ultimately resulted in adding more schools in the area of Jamnagar. She became aware of the importance of education and teaching as she worked on these projects. She wanted to ensure that everyone in India had access to affordable education. She is the chairperson of the Dhirubhai Ambani Foundation School, which was founded in 2003. The charitable division of Reliance Industries Ltd is called Reliance Foundation. She oversaw the foundation's initiatives in the fields of education, healthcare, art, and culture, as well as rural and urban change. Under her leadership, the Reliance Foundation has launched a number of projects, including the publication of a Hindi newspaper in Braille and cornea transplants, to name a few. Career After being elected to the Board of East India Hotels, the company that runs the Oberoi chain of hotels, Nita Ambani made her professional debut in the world of business. She later became the first female board member of Reliance Industries Ltd because of this position, which served as a launching pad for bigger things; she initiated a lot of business ventures. The co-ownership of the IPL cricket team, Mumbai Indians, was one of her largest commercial ventures. She acknowledged in one of her interviews that she had a long-standing love of cricket and had tried to learn as much as she could about the sport. The Mumbai Indians became the dominant team in the Indian Premier League thanks to her commitment to her club. In 2013, 2015, 2017, and 2019 the Mumbai Indians won the championship. She also established Football Sports Development Limited with the intention of popularizing sports in the nation. She is well known for having had a significant impact on amateur sports. Charitable Work Nita Ambani eventually had to stop teaching, but she couldn't hold back her enthusiasm for very long. She requested that they build schools in the adjacent rural communities while Mukesh Ambani was involved in building pipes in Patalganga. This ultimately resulted in adding more schools. While working on these projects, she realised how much education and teaching meant to her. She wanted to ensure that everyone in India had access to affordable education. Reliance Foundation is the name of the charitable arm of Nita Ambani's self-funded business, Reliance Industries Ltd. She handled the foundation's programmes for transformation in rural and urban areas, as well as in the areas of healthcare, art, and culture. Under her leadership, the Reliance Foundation has launched a number of projects, including the publication of a Hindi newspaper in Braille and cornea transplants, to name a few. Prizes and Honours With her tireless efforts to highlight sports and equitable education in India, Nita Ambani has managed to add a good number of accolades to her cap. Being presented with the Rashtriya Khel Protsahan Award 2017 by the Indian President is one of them. Additionally, she was given the Times of India's Best Corporate 